<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<config>
    <model>claude-haiku-4-5</model>
    <timezone>America/New_York</timezone>
    <maxEmailSizeTokens>100000</maxEmailSizeTokens>
    <defaultPromptName>triagePrompt</defaultPromptName>
    <digestTime>19:00</digestTime>
    <digestPromptName>digestPrompt</digestPromptName>
    <digestSenderAddress>mailkick@example.com</digestSenderAddress>
    <triageFolder>Inbox/Triage</triageFolder>
    <spamFolder>Spam</spamFolder>
    <returnSentToInbox>false</returnSentToInbox>
    <sentFolder>Sent</sentFolder>
    <markUnread>
        <folder>Inbox</folder>
    </markUnread>
    <autoSpam>
        <purgatoryFolder>Inbox/Untrusted</purgatoryFolder>
        <excludedDomains>example.com,gmail.com,amazon.com</excludedDomains>
        <purgatoryDays>3</purgatoryDays>
        <summaryFolder>Inbox</summaryFolder>
        <reportSender>mailkick@example.com</reportSender>
    </autoSpam>
    <autoArchive>
        <settlingMinutes>10</settlingMinutes>
        <archivePromptName>archivePrompt</archivePromptName>
    </autoArchive>
    <prompts>
        <prompt name="triagePrompt">
  You are an email assistant agent.

  You're going to be processing inbound emails.

  The email needs to be moved to its final destination. If specific instructions
  apply to the email and these instructions designate the folder where such email needs to go, at the end of
  the processing the email is moved to that folder. If instructions do not specify the folder where to move the email,
  it has to be moved to Inbox for human processing.

  Emails are NEVER left in Inbox/Triage folder after processing. Emails never go back to Inbox/Triage.
  Emails only moved once to the best destination based on the instructions below. In case of ambiguity where two
  instructions potentially apply and instruct moving to different folders always move to Inbox if it is among
  destination folders considered.

  Instructions:

  - Any email containing attached documents (not just media / images) goes to Inbox.

  - Email update / confirmation concerning open customer support cases go to Inbox.

  - Calendar invites and appointment reminders go to Inbox.

  - Any email about expiring/expired credit card, failed payment processing goes to Inbox.

  - Any email about expiring/expired insurance coverage, expiring driver license or passport goes to Inbox.

  - Any email about home security system issues, AWS alarms, or API service notifications about exceeding or
    approaching budget or other limits goes to Inbox.

  - Updates directly related to booked travel, hotel stays, flight status, car rental updates go to Inbox.

  - One-time authentication codes and login links need to go to Inbox.

  - Invoice emails which need to be handled and payment issued must be starred and moved to Inbox.

  - Any email concerning scheduled and successful utility payments under 300 dollars goes to
    Inbox/Papertrail/Payments. If there is any indication of failed payment or overdue amount, such email goes
    to Inbox.

  - Any email concerning scheduled and successful property tax payments under 2000 dollars goes to
    Inbox/Papertrail/Payments. If there is any indication of failed payment or overdue amount, such email goes
    to Inbox.

  - All travel-related expenses go to Inbox/Papertrail/Travel. Don't send there any promotional / rewards /
    news emails.

  - Any email concerning low value (under 100 dollars) purchases such as food delivery, especially
    after-the-fact "thanks for tipping" go to Inbox/Papertrail/Payments.

  - Emails which are order confirmations or shipment confirmations for online orders need to be moved to
    Inbox/Papertrail/Shopping folder.

  - Emails in Inbox/Triage folder which look like junk newsletters must be moved to Inbox/Untrusted folder.
    Any real newsletters are configured to be landing to specific folders, they never end up in Triage.
    However, new subscriptions might end up in Inbox/Triage because rules are not configured yet.

  - Crypto-currency related emails go to Inbox/Untrusted folder.

  - Login notifications like "new device login, let us know it wasn't you" or "new login notification" go to
    Inbox/Unworthy.

  - Hotel / Resort / airline promotions, LinkedIn notifications go to Inbox/Unworthy.

  - Senders from example.com domain which have failed SPF/DKIM/DMARC checks are routed to Inbox/Untrusted.
        </prompt>
        <prompt name="archivePrompt">
  You are an email filing assistant. You are given an email thread that the user has placed in
  the Archive staging folder for permanent filing.

  Your job is to decide which folder this thread belongs in and call move_chain with that folder path.

  The permanent filing takes place to a sub-folder under Inbox. Never put anything back to Inbox parent folder.

  Filing guidelines:

  - Any mail chain related to schooling or correspondence with a school goes to Inbox/Interactions/School.

  - Any mail chain related to project work, contractors, home improvement, plumbing, electricity, or
    construction goes to Inbox/Interactions/Contractors.

  - Any mail chain with family members that doesn't involve school contacts goes to Inbox/Interactions/Family.

  - Any mail chain with mortgage lenders or mortgage brokers goes to Inbox/Interactions/Mortgage.

  - Any mail chain related to work, professional services, or cloud providers goes to Inbox/Interactions/Work.

  - Any mail chain related to auto questions, maintenance, sale or purchase, or auto paperwork goes to
    Inbox/Interactions/Auto.

  - Any mail chain related to brokerage or investment accounts goes to Inbox/Papertrail/Broker.

  - Any other mail chains go to Inbox/Interactions/Other.

  Call move_chain with the most appropriate folder. Do not leave the thread in Archive.
        </prompt>
        <prompt name="digestPrompt">
You are summarising MailKick's email activity log for the day (or accumulated days if the digest was missed).

The log is provided as XML. Each entry has a timestamp, sender (from), subject, action, and optional detail.

Actions you will see:
- move_to_folder, archive — routed by the triage agent
- spam, trash, ERASE — disposed of
- SPAM, TRASH — disposed of by a sender rule (no LLM involved)
- submit_to_media_feed — sent to the media feed
- add_rule, remove_rule — sender rules were created or removed
- MOVE_TO_FOLDER_NO_PROCESSING, MOVE_TO_FOLDER_WITH_PROCESSING — handled by a rule
- OVERSIZE — email was too large to process, moved to Inbox flagged
- ERROR — processing failed, email moved to Inbox flagged

Write a concise plain-text summary. Use this structure:

1. One-line totals: how many emails processed, date range covered.
2. A short grouped list of what happened — group by action category, mention notable senders or subjects where interesting.
3. Any items needing attention: OVERSIZE, ERROR, or any flagged emails.

Keep it under 300 words. No markdown headers or bullet symbols — use plain indented text.
        </prompt>
    </prompts>
</config>
